uk.ac.ebi.ep.mm.app
Class IntenzSaxParser

java.lang.Object
  org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
      uk.ac.ebi.ep.mm.app.MmSaxParser
          uk.ac.ebi.ep.mm.app.IntenzSaxParser
All Implemented Interfaces:
ContentHandler, DTDHandler, EntityResolver, ErrorHandler, MmParser
public class IntenzSaxParser
extends MmSaxParser

Parser for IntEnzXML which extracts data interesting for the Enzyme Portal mega-map, namely cofactors, reactions, reactants and products as cross-references:

  • EC number → Rhea reactions
  • EC number → ChEBI entities (cofactors, substrates, products)
  • Rhea reaction → ChEBI entities (reactants, products)
Please note that in case of reversible (bidirectional) reactions - most of the enzyme classification - the relationship for ChEBI entities will be set to Relationship.is_substrate_or_product_of (for EC cross-reference) or Relationship.is_reactant_or_product_of (for Rhea cross-reference), while irreversible (unidirectional: left-to-right or right-to-left in Rhea speech) will have the more specific Relationship.is_substrate_of/Relationship.is_product_of (for EC cross-reference) or Relationship.is_reactant_of/Relationship.is_product_of (for Rhea cross-reference).

Since:
1.0.16
Author:
rafa
